detailedDescription.articleBody: Iran Khodro, branded as IKCO, is an Iranian automaker headquartered in Tehran. The company's original name was Irannational. IKCO was founded in 1962 and it produced 688,000 passenger cars in 2009.

detailedDescription.articleBody:
IKCO EF engines are a family of four-cylinder engines. The EF7 series are designed jointly by Iran Khodro Powertrain Company and F.E.V GmbH of Germany. The other models will be designed by IPCO itself. IPCO is the powertrain designing & producing company of Iranian car manufacturer Iran Khodro. IKCO aims to supply 800,000 powertrains by 2010.
The first phase of IKCO EF Engines project investments were about 80 million US$.
EF4 & EF7 engines use CNG as their main fuel and they can also use gasoline. EFD is the first engine of the EF family that is single-fuel. It uses high-quality diesel as fuel.
EF engines share most of their parts between them.
